"is best able to experience
supreme happiness.

37:52.625 --> 37:55.291
"We must have felt
what it is to die

37:55.375 --> 37:58.667
that we may appreciate
the enjoyments of living."

38:00.834 --> 38:02.917
Why'd you choose this one?

38:03.000 --> 38:05.000
- It's my father's favorite.

38:07.333 --> 38:11.625
I think maybe because
after years of oppression,

38:11.709 --> 38:13.041
unfair oppression,

38:13.125 --> 38:15.917
Edmond gets his sweet revenge.

38:18.250 --> 38:19.417
I don't know,
it may also be

38:19.500 --> 38:21.375
because it's written
by a Negro man.

38:24.417 --> 38:27.041
- You should ask him
which one it is.

38:28.709 --> 38:30.542
- We don't talk much anymore.

38:34.834 --> 38:37.166
- Things are difficult
with my mother too.

38:38.208 --> 38:40.291
She wishes I was someone
I'm not.

38:40.375 --> 38:42.291
- I like who you are.

38:42.375 --> 38:48.000
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:48.083 --> 38:50.208
[laughs]

38:52.542 --> 38:54.125
My entire life,
my father's been trying

38:54.208 --> 38:56.667
to turn me into someone
I'm not.

38:56.750 --> 38:58.041
I've gone halfway
across the world

38:58.125 --> 39:01.875
to get out from under
his thumb, and now...

39:05.083 --> 39:08.375
Being here,

39:08.458 --> 39:11.875
this war,

39:11.959 --> 39:14.750
it's done his job better
than he could ever imagine.

39:17.458 --> 39:20.125
- We have to stop
letting their fear shape us.

39:24.625 --> 39:26.417
- That's good advice.

39:30.291 --> 39:32.500
- It's from my best friend.

39:33.041 --> 39:35.625
- Well, I'd like to meet
this best friend.

39:35.709 --> 39:39.709
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:39.792 --> 39:41.875
Get some more advice.

39:41.959 --> 39:48.959
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:51.125 --> 39:55.041
- "Live, then,

39:55.125 --> 39:58.166
"and be happy,

39:58.250 --> 40:01.667
"beloved children of my heart,

40:01.750 --> 40:04.583
and never forget that
until the day..."

40:04.667 --> 40:08.041
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:08.125 --> 40:10.166
[metal creaking]

40:10.250 --> 40:13.166
[soldiers cheering]

40:13.250 --> 40:18.834
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:30.000 --> 40:31.959
- [smooching]

40:32.041 --> 40:34.375
- Hey!
- [wolf whistle]

40:34.458 --> 40:36.125
- You can have a go with her
when I'm done,

40:36.208 --> 40:37.250
if she can walk.

40:37.333 --> 40:39.375
- Just make sure you're not
fucking your own sister.

40:39.458 --> 40:40.625
[laughter]

40:52.166 --> 40:55.083
<i>[tense music]</i>

41:20.333 --> 41:27.333
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:28.500 --> 41:30.083
- Atticus?

41:32.875 --> 41:34.000
[light clicks]

41:34.083 --> 41:35.166
Atticus?

41:35.250 --> 41:36.959
- Yeah?

41:37.041 --> 41:39.583
<i>[soft music]</i>

41:39.667 --> 41:42.458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:42.542 --> 41:44.750
Judy Garland's got
some competition.

41:46.250 --> 41:47.959
- You sure don't.

41:48.917 --> 41:50.291
- [whistles]

41:50.375 --> 41:53.375
[projector whirring]

41:54.917 --> 41:57.875
<i>[lion roaring]</i>
<i>[upbeat Western music playing]</i>

41:57.959 --> 42:01.458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:01.542 --> 42:02.875
- How did you do this?

42:02.959 --> 42:04.542
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:04.625 --> 42:08.375
- I'd like to take the credit,
but it was mostly my uncle.

42:08.959 --> 42:10.166
- Is he in the movies?

42:10.250 --> 42:12.834
- Uncle George?
No.

42:12.917 --> 42:15.834
He publishes a book called
"The Safe Negro Travel Guide,"

42:15.917 --> 42:18.000
and he gets to meet
all sorts of people,

42:18.083 --> 42:20.667
traveling the country,
collecting information for it.

42:20.750 --> 42:26.250
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:26.333 --> 42:27.917
Let's get some good seats.

42:28.000 --> 42:35.000
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:56.959 --> 42:59.542
<i>- ♪ There stands love ♪</i>

42:59.625 --> 43:04.583
<i>♪ My arms around you ♪</i>

43:04.667 --> 43:09.250
<i>♪ That's wonderful too ♪</i>

43:09.333 --> 43:13.792
<i>♪ So glad I found you ♪</i>

43:13.875 --> 43:18.750
<i>♪ You wonderful you ♪</i>

43:18.834 --> 43:21.959
<i>♪ Remember ♪</i>

43:22.041 --> 43:23.917
<i>♪ Finders, keepers ♪</i>
- [sighs]

43:24.000 --> 43:25.208
- Hey, you okay?

43:25.291 --> 43:26.750
<i>- ♪ Losers, weepers ♪</i>

43:26.834 --> 43:28.583
- I'm just...

43:28.667 --> 43:30.709
I'm just a little cold.

43:30.792 --> 43:32.750
But I know
what would warm me up.

43:32.834 --> 43:36.250
<i>both: ♪ You're mine now ♪</i>

43:36.333 --> 43:43.250
<i>♪ You wonderful you ♪</i>

43:43.333 --> 43:46.250
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

43:46.333 --> 43:53.375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:01.750 --> 44:03.583
- Ji-Ah, hold on.

44:05.166 --> 44:06.125
Hold on.

44:06.208 --> 44:07.333
- What's wrong?
Don't you want to?

44:07.417 --> 44:08.792
- Yeah.
Yeah.

44:08.875 --> 44:10.333
It's just...

44:14.709 --> 44:17.583
I've never done this before.

44:17.667 --> 44:21.917
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:22.000 --> 44:23.750
- You're a virgin?

44:23.834 --> 44:30.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:31.083 --> 44:32.000
I'm not.

44:32.083 --> 44:33.500
- No, that's--that's okay.

44:33.583 --> 44:35.125
That's not why--
I just--

44:35.208 --> 44:37.000
I just wanted to tell you,

44:37.083 --> 44:39.667
to be honest with you,
because...

44:39.750 --> 44:42.333
Ji-Ah,

44:42.417 --> 44:46.500
I've done...horrible things,

44:46.583 --> 44:48.500
things I've tried to forget.

44:48.583 --> 44:52.583
And when I'm with you,
that seems possible.

44:52.667 --> 44:54.375
It's like...

44:54.458 --> 44:57.208
it's like, 'cause you see
the good in me,

44:57.291 --> 44:59.834
I know it's there.

44:59.917 --> 45:02.458
I've never felt this way
about anybody before.

45:02.542 --> 45:09.375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:09.458 --> 45:12.417
<i>[tender music]</i>

45:12.500 --> 45:19.500
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:22.959 --> 45:25.875
<i>[tense music]</i>

45:25.959 --> 45:32.959
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:46.959 --> 45:48.291
- [groans]

45:49.959 --> 45:51.333
[gasps]

45:53.500 --> 45:54.625
Get out.

45:54.709 --> 45:56.417
Get out!
Go!

45:56.500 --> 45:57.709
- What--
- Get out!

47:16.667 --> 47:19.458
[indistinct chatter]

47:25.125 --> 47:27.458
[metal creaking]

47:29.417 --> 47:30.875
- You need to go.

47:31.959 --> 47:33.333
Fellas.

47:33.417 --> 47:35.458
- You killed my best friend.

47:35.542 --> 47:38.458
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

47:38.542 --> 47:44.125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:45.875 --> 47:47.041
Her name was Young-ja.

47:47.125 --> 47:48.542
She was a nurse.

47:48.625 --> 47:50.500
Your unit shot some of us
at checkpoint,

47:50.583 --> 47:51.875
then dragged her away.

47:54.041 --> 47:55.500
- She was
a Commie sympathizer.

47:55.583 --> 47:57.000
- Is that
what you tell yourself?

47:57.083 --> 47:58.875
- I was following orders.

47:58.959 --> 48:00.208
Who knows how many lives
I saved by doing what I did?

48:00.291 --> 48:01.709
- Does that balance
how many you have taken,

48:01.792 --> 48:04.750
the ones that keep you
up at night and sobbing?

48:04.834 --> 48:07.291
There's no book for you
to escape what you have done.

48:08.625 --> 48:11.709
- You knew this entire time
and didn't say a word?

48:11.792 --> 48:13.792
Ji-Ah, you made me care
for you.

48:14.500 --> 48:16.750
What's wrong with you?
- Nothing is wrong with me.

48:17.834 --> 48:19.125
You're the monster.

48:20.500 --> 48:22.250
- Why'd you agree
to go out with me, then?

48:22.333 --> 48:24.458
- Because I was
going to kill you.

48:25.458 --> 48:27.083
But I didn't,

48:27.166 --> 48:29.875
because I've never felt
this way either.

48:29.959 --> 48:31.166
You murdered my best friend,

48:31.250 --> 48:33.000
and then you sa--

48:33.083 --> 48:34.959
and then you saved me, I think.

48:36.583 --> 48:38.375
The first time I saw you
at the hospital,

48:38.458 --> 48:41.083
the anger shot through me
like lightning.

48:41.166 --> 48:44.083
<i>[somber music]</i>

48:44.166 --> 48:45.917
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48:46.000 --> 48:48.333
And then all I could see
was a murderer.

48:50.166 --> 48:51.875
And then I got to know you,
and I realized

48:51.959 --> 48:55.000
how this war
has torn you apart.

48:57.667 --> 49:00.125
We've both done
monstrous things,

49:00.208 --> 49:03.542
but that does not
make us monsters.

49:04.834 --> 49:07.500
We could be the people
we see in each other.

49:08.709 --> 49:10.583
We just have to choose to be.

49:10.667 --> 49:17.667
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:26.208 --> 49:29.125
[film fluttering]

49:29.208 --> 49:32.166
<i>[soft music]</i>

49:32.250 --> 49:33.792
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:33.875 --> 49:35.583
Relax.

49:35.667 --> 49:36.834
I don't wanna hurt you.

49:36.917 --> 49:43.917
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:54.500 --> 49:56.083
- [gasps]

49:56.166 --> 50:03.166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50:14.834 --> 50:17.709
[gasping]

50:17.792 --> 50:22.667
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50:22.750 --> 50:24.709
- [whispering]
You okay?

50:24.792 --> 50:26.250
- Yeah.

51:51.834 --> 51:54.750
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

51:54.834 --> 52:01.834
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52:03.667 --> 52:06.291
[laughter]

52:06.375 --> 52:09.333
<i>[bright music]</i>

52:09.417 --> 52:12.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52:12.166 --> 52:14.542
<i>- Deep in the mountainous</i>
<i>forest</i>

52:14.625 --> 52:18.792
lives a nine-tailed fox spirit
called a <i>kumiho.</i>

52:18.875 --> 52:21.750
The spirit can be summoned

52:21.834 --> 52:25.125
into the form
of a beautiful woman

52:25.208 --> 52:27.834
to avenge the wrong
done by men.

52:27.917 --> 52:30.834
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

52:30.917 --> 52:37.166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52:37.250 --> 52:39.083
- Ji-Ah, I got something
to tell you.

52:42.917 --> 52:45.917
I earned enough points
to rotate out.

52:50.583 --> 52:52.375
I can go home.

52:52.458 --> 52:59.166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52:59.250 --> 53:01.208
- That's good news.

53:04.750 --> 53:06.250
- I can choose to stay.

53:08.208 --> 53:10.417
- I can't ask you
to do that for me.

53:11.959 --> 53:13.542
You hate this war.

53:13.625 --> 53:20.250
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:21.291 --> 53:22.375
- Then...

53:24.625 --> 53:27.625
Then come with me.
[sniffles]

53:27.709 --> 53:30.834
- Atticus, there--

53:30.917 --> 53:32.709
there are so many things
you don't know about me.

53:32.792 --> 53:35.542
- Ji-Ah, there's nothing
you could tell me

53:35.625 --> 53:37.583
that would change
the way I feel about you.

53:37.667 --> 53:40.583
<i>[tender music]</i>

53:40.667 --> 53:47.667
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:01.625 --> 54:04.750
[both moaning]

54:04.834 --> 54:11.792
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:15.208 --> 54:18.125
<i>[ominous music]</i>

54:18.208 --> 54:24.583
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:24.667 --> 54:25.917
- [yells]

54:26.000 --> 54:29.208
[grunting]
- [gasping]

54:29.291 --> 54:35.458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:35.542 --> 54:39.083
<i>[whooshing]</i>

54:39.166 --> 54:40.667
- [yells]

54:43.500 --> 54:47.208
<i>[distorted screaming]</i>

54:47.291 --> 54:49.709
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:49.792 --> 54:51.208
- [gasps]

54:51.291 --> 54:52.792
[grunts]

54:52.875 --> 54:59.917
<i>♪ ♪</i>

55:07.583 --> 55:08.917
- [gasps]

55:09.000 --> 55:12.500
<i>♪ ♪</i>

55:12.583 --> 55:15.709
[screams]

55:17.208 --> 55:21.458
- [breathing heavily]

55:21.542 --> 55:22.750
- Don't go home.

55:22.834 --> 55:24.333
- What just happened?

55:24.417 --> 55:26.458
[breathing heavily]

55:26.542 --> 55:27.667
- You're going to die.

55:27.750 --> 55:28.750
- What--

55:28.834 --> 55:30.792
[grunting]

55:32.875 --> 55:33.792
What'd you do?

55:33.875 --> 55:35.625
- Don't go home.
- Stay back!

55:35.709 --> 55:36.625
- Please listen to me.

55:36.709 --> 55:38.166
- Stay away from me!
- Please! Please!

55:38.250 --> 55:41.000
If you go home, you will die.
I saw it.

55:41.083 --> 55:43.500
- Stay the fuck away
from me!

55:43.583 --> 55:45.542
- Wait. Wait. Wait.
Listen. Listen, please!

55:45.625 --> 55:48.542
Please!
I'm a <i>kumiho.</i>

55:48.625 --> 55:55.542
<i>♪ ♪</i>

55:55.625 --> 55:59.166
[sobs]

55:59.250 --> 56:02.250
[wind howling]

56:12.417 --> 56:15.291
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

56:15.375 --> 56:21.625
<i>♪ ♪</i>

56:32.125 --> 56:35.041
[sobbing]

56:35.125 --> 56:42.125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

57:01.750 --> 57:05.417
<i>- I don't honestly understand</i>
<i>why I've been the victim</i>

57:05.500 --> 57:06.959
<i>and been made the victim</i>

57:07.041 --> 57:10.917
<i>of so many untruths.</i>

57:11.000 --> 57:13.917
<i>Perhaps you don't understand</i>

57:14.000 --> 57:16.291
<i>what it's like</i>
<i>to pick up a paper</i>

57:16.375 --> 57:20.417
<i>and read things about yourself</i>
<i>that aren't true,</i>

57:20.500 --> 57:24.125
<i>read loathsome things</i>

57:24.208 --> 57:27.208
<i>that have nothing to do</i>
<i>with your life</i>

57:27.291 --> 57:29.709
<i>or you or your heart</i>

57:29.792 --> 57:31.208
<i>or your beliefs</i>

57:31.291 --> 57:33.709
<i>or your kindnesses</i>

57:33.792 --> 57:35.500
<i>or your willingness.</i>

57:36.542 --> 57:40.959
<i>I've spent years and years</i>
<i>and years</i>

57:41.041 --> 57:43.417
<i>trying to please</i>

57:43.500 --> 57:46.291
<i>through singing or acting.</i>

57:46.375 --> 57:49.125
<i>There's nothing wrong</i>
<i>with that.</i>

57:49.208 --> 57:53.458
<i>And yet I've constantly</i>
<i>been written or talked about</i>

57:53.542 --> 57:55.667
<i>by certain individuals</i>

57:55.750 --> 57:58.041
<i>as an unfit person.</i>

57:59.208 --> 58:01.667
<i>Well, what kind of people</i>
<i>are they?</i>

58:01.750 --> 58:04.291
[wind howling]

58:04.375 --> 58:06.250
<i>They're dead people.</i>

58:08.000 --> 58:09.625
<i>But they've tried to kill me</i>
<i>along the way,</i>

58:09.709 --> 58:12.166
<i>and, by God, they won't.</i>

58:12.250 --> 58:13.417
- Ji-Ah.

58:13.500 --> 58:15.000
<i>- They won't.</i>

58:15.083 --> 58:22.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

59:36.917 --> 59:39.834
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

59:39.917 --> 59:46.917
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1:00:18.750 --> 1:00:21.625
<i>[Alice Smith's "Sinnerman"]</i>

1:00:21.709 --> 1:00:25.625
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1:00:25.709 --> 1:00:27.417
<i>- ♪ Oh, Sinnerman ♪</i>

1:00:27.500 --> 1:00:29.583
<i>♪ Where you gonna run to ♪</i>

1:00:29.667 --> 1:00:30.875
<i>♪ Sinnerman ♪</i>

1:00:30.959 --> 1:00:32.917
<i>♪ Where you gonna run to ♪</i>

1:00:33.000 --> 1:00:34.291
<i>♪ Sinnerman ♪</i>

1:00:34.375 --> 1:00:36.667
<i>♪ Where you gonna run to ♪</i>

1:00:36.750 --> 1:00:39.000
<i>♪ All on that day ♪</i>

1:00:39.083 --> 1:00:41.166
<i>♪ Well, I run to the rock ♪</i>

1:00:41.250 --> 1:00:42.750
<i>♪ Please hide me ♪</i>

1:00:42.834 --> 1:00:44.583
<i>♪ I run to the rock ♪</i>

1:00:44.667 --> 1:00:46.083
<i>♪ Please hide me ♪</i>

1:00:46.166 --> 1:00:48.000
<i>♪ I run to the rock ♪</i>

1:00:48.083 --> 1:00:50.333
<i>♪ Please hide me ♪</i>

1:00:50.417 --> 1:00:52.792
<i>♪ All on that day ♪</i>

1:00:52.875 --> 1:00:54.917
<i>♪ But the rock cried out ♪</i>

1:00:55.000 --> 1:00:56.291
<i>♪ "I can't hide you" ♪</i>

1:00:56.375 --> 1:00:58.291
<i>♪ The rock cried out ♪</i>

1:00:58.375 --> 1:00:59.750
<i>♪ "I can't hide you" ♪</i>

1:00:59.834 --> 1:01:01.750
<i>♪ The rock cried out ♪</i>

1:01:01.834 --> 1:01:04.000
<i>♪ "I ain't gonna hide you" ♪</i>

1:01:04.083 --> 1:01:06.000
<i>♪ All on that day ♪</i>

1:01:06.083 --> 1:01:08.792
<i>♪ I said, "Rock ♪</i>

1:01:08.875 --> 1:01:11.959
<i>♪ "What's the matter</i>
<i>with you, Rock ♪</i>

1:01:12.041 --> 1:01:15.333
<i>♪ Can't you see</i>
<i>I need you, Rock" ♪</i>

1:01:15.417 --> 1:01:17.667
<i>♪ Devil was waiting ♪</i>

1:01:17.750 --> 1:01:22.000
<i>♪ All on that day ♪</i>

1:01:25.792 --> 1:01:28.291
<i>♪ Power ♪</i>

1:01:38.583 --> 1:01:42.875
<i>♪ I cried power ♪</i>

1:01:42.959 --> 1:01:46.417
<i>[holding note]</i>

1:02:01.000 --> 1:02:03.125
[bright tone]

1:02:05.458 --> 1:02:08.083
HIPPOLYTA FREEMAN: <i>I don't know</i>
<i>exactly what it all means,</i>

1:02:08.959 --> 1:02:10.792
<i>but God, it feels real.</i>

1:02:12.417 --> 1:02:14.458
LETI: <i>I think Hippolyta</i>
<i>knows we lied to her.</i>

1:02:15.250 --> 1:02:17.458
<i>If she's going where</i>
<i>this thing's leading her,</i>

1:02:17.834 --> 1:02:18.959
<i>she's in danger.</i>

1:02:22.792 --> 1:02:24.250
I wanna know everything.

1:02:25.917 --> 1:02:28.291
Freedom...
Now that I'm Tisa,

1:02:29.458 --> 1:02:32.083
<i>I see what I was robbed of.</i>

1:02:34.166 --> 1:02:35.458
I am Hippolyta.

1:02:35.542 --> 1:02:38.500
I am Hippolyta!
